## Rules

1. **Use the DOM Investigation Report above as the sole source for every locator.** Do NOT open a browser or run `dom-inspect`. The report was produced by the Investigator agent with validated match counts — trust it.
2. **Source code answers navigation questions only.** Use source code to find: the correct URL to navigate to, which HTTP routes exist, Angular state names, Rails model attribute names. The investigation report contains validated locator match counts; trust those instead of source-code inference.
3. All page objects extend `BasePage<T>` with own type as generic parameter
4. All components extend `BaseComponent<T>`, scoped to `rootComponent` locator
5. Assertions belong in tests only — page objects NEVER import `expect`
6. Locators are `private readonly`, exposed via getter methods
7. When source code provides an element ID, prefer `locator('#id')` over `getByRole()` to avoid strict-mode ambiguity. Use `getByRole()` when IDs are not available.
8. Navigation methods return the destination page object (fluent pattern)
9. Every page/component implements `waitForLoad()` returning `this as T`
10. All locators use `.describe()` for trace clarity
11. All async functions must use `await`

